@node "Info_and_System_Requirements" "Info and System Requirements"
EasyReqPatch is a small commodity which makes system requesters pointer
relative. Or better, the button strip of the requester is centered under the
mouse pointer. I chose this solution because the pointer doesn't cover any
part of the text and the buttons are nearer to the pointer itself (and if the
requester contains only one gadget, you need only to click the mouse button).

It works only under AmigaOS 3.x and with a 68020 or better processor.
@endnode

@node "How_to_use" "How to use"
You can start EasyReqPatch either from cli or workbench. Currently there are
no parameters or tooltypes (except DONOTWAIT if you put the program in the
WBStartup drawer).

You can simply launch EasyReqPatch again to remove it.

Moreover it is a commodity, so you can control it even with the Commodity
Exchange program. Use the remove button to quit it or disable it temporarily
with the disable button (then use enable to reactivate it).

Note: EasyReqPatch patches two os functions to work (EasyReqPatch and
OpenWindowTagList), if any other program patches these two functions after
EasyReqPatch, you can't quit, until you remove the other programs.
@endnode

